g agents. Three patients discontinued Nif-CC, two as ordered by their primary care physician and one on his own due to headache.\\ This study suggests that patients switched from Nif-GITS to Nif-CC could experience increased blood pressure during the night or toward the end of the dosing interval. They could also experience adverse effects such as headache, edema, and dizziness, which could result in more physician visits and put patients with other disease states such as coronary heart disease at increased risk.]
